transcript_text: If you have knee pain, such as when doing squats, it is very likely that in this day  and age due to all the sitting that everyone does that it's because you have tight quads  and in particular your rack fam.  This is a great stretch to loosen that muscle and your quad and hip flexor in general.  As you may have noticed, I squeezed my glue to push my pelvis forward a little more which  will further increase the stretch.  If you want to incorporate or emphasize the hip flexor more, lean forward as I am here and  if you want to focus on the quad more, lean back and try to touch your butt to your heel.
